	('8def6180-f72c-453b-a6f4-3be33bb47dcc','infrastructure-a629-halifax-town-centre-corridor-improvement-phase-2-calderdale',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:19.902','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Galliford Try\'s Infrastructure business was appointed by Calderdale Council to a £34 million scheme through the YORcivil framework for the A629 Halifax Town Centre Corridor Improvement (Phase 2). The project aims to revitalize the town centre through pedestrianisation of key access areas, re-routing railway station access, and redesigning road layouts to encourage sustainable transport.','Infrastructure business Galliford Try appointed to £34m Halifax regeneration scheme','Galliford Try','2024-02-22 00:00:00.000','https://www.gallifordtry.co.uk/news/infrastructure-business-appointed-to-halifax-regeneration-scheme','Galliford Try\'s Infrastructure business was appointed by Calderdale Council to a £34 million scheme through the YORcivil framework for the A629 Halifax Town Centre Corridor Improvement (Phase 2). The project aims to revitalize the town centre through pedestrianisation of key access areas, re-routing railway station access, and redesigning road layouts to encourage sustainable transport.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('8df8787f-4283-4e34-b419-ac29b7084dbf','infrastructure-five-towns-leisure-hub-wakefield',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.669','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'A STATE-OF-THE-ART £21million sports and leisure facility has completed in Pontefract, West Yorkshire thanks to leading architecture studio GT3 Architects and national contractor Willmott Dixon. Aspire@ThePark offers state-of-the-art sports facilities to five towns surrounding Wakefield city. The development has recently opened its doors to the public in line with government guidance. [7], [9]','WEST YORKSHIRE GETS MOVING WITH COMPLETED £21M LEISURE CENTRE','e-architect / Architecture Today','2021-08-03 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFRMpqaAN_kv4YiwaTBjlGTv4mfEEU8gmDhfNwKKc2e8IXpIX8ek3LTO-y-EG_QNQ-nJiAXTEZwiO1gRaIGhSCYoUEq79o9c-BmwRrm8PNGiZKv5sjaLAnNoS6ebk38EwD0A63CfggmJ6PGiHrA19Evebv6XXhAUr0NrEU=','The state-of-the-art £21 million Aspire@ThePark sports and leisure facility in Pontefract, West Yorkshire, completed construction and recently opened its doors to the public in line with government guidance. Designed by GT3 Architects and built by Willmott Dixon, it offers a 10-lane 25m swimming pool, 100-station fitness suite, climbing zone, café, and a full-size 3G football pitch.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('8e5d8eed-aae6-4b50-8452-bda0ec3ccf47','infrastructure-aire-park-development',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:19.453','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'The first phase of Aire Park reached structural completion back in February 2023. However, work on the 200,000 sq. ft. of commercial space\'s interior is to continue. [...] The second phase of Aire Park began in early May 2023. [...] Tetley\'s former headquarters, Huntsman House, is being demolished. It began in early April 2023 and should take two months to complete. This is to make space for the new recreational space. [5]','First Phase Commercial Buildings Reach Structural Completion; Second Phase Commences','CityRise','2023-05-25 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH1r4N5N-5XQCRNfnq7oco3zGCpoPIyhxZRC9b1mEt9dzUgPTQKFqla-wh_SOsVw-U0kp6XEkQ-14-TOdXBTgdysH_oP1D2QLkJkT3o_BaKgbRxbDAHVWOlEHGnF5vDyGYakodW5JSfWawGcMBAjKMRn2M [5]','The first phase of Aire Park\'s commercial development, comprising two office buildings, reached structural completion in February 2023. Concurrently, the second phase of the project began in early May 2023, which included the start of demolition for Tetley\'s former headquarters to make way for new recreational space.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('8ecc77cd-bbae-46e1-a13b-3f2da814dc38','infrastructure-bradford-live-odeon-theatre-transformation',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.098','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'The West Yorkshire Combined Authority (WYCA) announced a £325,000 grant for the Bradford Odeon renovation, part of the Leeds City Region\'s Growth Deal. This funding was released after the NEC Group was confirmed as the operating partner, pledging an additional £2 million. The project was expected to open in 2020.','Bradford Odeon grant released after operator found','The Business Desk','2017-09-14 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE1ktyeMpE0_HyZGZGg0fGaebmNqIigEFAYq-6DDQSSqvoUY0Oqkqgoq5vPh2FkLYKLWbCzJhnBkvGw-qcpt_pGB4-HtbvA-wKMov0nLXOlhhovOwmxxTEt2vxNvPMq1vk4PN2qLDq95kCR-nB677XHRV9wdjXSlbbQ4u6RrPuRQlvTYpKuXg7UfYhP_2yn7olwCZfqV_0RI-Q-goaw','The West Yorkshire Combined Authority (WYCA) announced a £325,000 grant for the Bradford Odeon renovation, part of the Leeds City Region\'s Growth Deal. This funding was released after the NEC Group was confirmed as the operating partner, pledging an additional £2 million. The project was expected to open in 2020.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('8ff7d69c-57e3-4ee6-9a08-4cf151c3f36b','infrastructure-frizinghall-station-revitalization',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.032','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Frizinghall. Opened: 1875, Closed: 1965, Reopened: 1987. History: Our current campaigns for the station: Provide Sunday services to Leeds; Increase services to 4 per hour.','Frizinghall | Bradford Rail Users Group','Bradford Rail Users Group','1987-09-07 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG8XDEW0cHl-w42ynvcvPVJrfKD9w1CcoMbJupaWtzfMT15YoEshaySSIDicIfcnc4GJgVhn600upuBcZqYgbTGXgtJ7YTsqh0t1XFIO1bIZOTn8HNRwA8qz_rXH1w-vPWk1Qs5ngev-edM8fse','The Bradford Rail Users Group page for Frizinghall station confirms its opening, closure, and reopening dates (1875, 1965, 1987). It also outlines current campaigns for the station, such as providing Sunday services to Leeds and increasing service frequency, indicating ongoing efforts for functional improvements and revitalization beyond physical aesthetics.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('90251bfb-d324-410a-a6db-9cf87e2a4766','infrastructure-aldi-retail-park-leeds-tunstall-road-ev-charger',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.417','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Aldi Retail Park - Leeds - Pod Point. Tunstall Road, Leeds, United Kingdom. Ladestation med ladestander for elbil. Opladningsstedet har 4 ladepunkter på max 7 kW. Denne ladestander tilhører Pod Point. Placeringsoplysninger. This is an open charge unit installed at the Aldi super store site in Tunstall Road, Leeds. © 2025 - ChargeFinder - Ladestandere til elbiler.','Aldi Retail Park - Leeds - Pod Point EV Charging Stations','ChargeFinder','2025-09-16 00:00:00.000','https://chargefinder.com/en/charging-station/aldi-retail-park-leeds-pod-point-80365','This entry on ChargeFinder confirms the presence of four Pod Point electric vehicle charging units at the Aldi superstore located on Tunstall Road, Leeds. Each charger has a maximum capacity of 7 kW. The entry specifies that these are open charge units. While no specific installation date is provided, the information confirms the operational status of the chargers at this location.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('905a2d6f-dc86-4fd6-a489-184cddfbb88a','infrastructure-south-village-formerly-leeds-city-one',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:19.503','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Developer Caddick submitted outline plans on July 25, 2022, for a new landmark development in Leeds, initially named \'City One Leeds\', to be built at the emerging South Bank neighbourhood. The plans included nearly 2,000 homes, 650,000 sq ft of offices, retail, leisure and community uses, and a new linear park along Sweet Street. The site is a brownfield area off Meadow Road. [13]','Outline plans in for 2,000 flats Leeds landmark scheme','Construction Enquirer News','2022-07-25 00:00:00.000','https://www.constructionenquirer.com/2022/07/25/outline-plans-in-for-2000-flats-leeds-landmark-scheme/','Developer Caddick submitted outline plans for a new landmark development in Leeds\' South Bank, then called \'City One Leeds\', proposing nearly 2,000 homes, alongside 650,000 sq ft of offices, retail, leisure, and community uses, plus a new linear park along Sweet Street. The brownfield site is located off Meadow Road.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('90b46928-8fed-4824-8d25-61b054ee12fb','infrastructure-a629-halifax-to-huddersfield-corridor-improvement-phase-4-calderdale',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:19.884','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Between Tuesday 26 October 2021 and midnight on Tuesday 23 November 2021, we are asking for your feedback on the latest designs. Your views are important as we shape designs, so please take this opportunity to let us know what you think. We will use the feedback we receive to refine the proposals before we appoint a contractor to build the scheme. We hope to begin construction in 2022.','A629 phase 4 walking and cycling Halifax - Huddersfield | Calderdale Next Chapter','Calderdale Next Chapter / Calderdale Council','2021-10-26 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGTdvNaNAYEWROrpoxVHTo4crGhI3lL3meJf-upI-nXxvnRIpxdms6r947FgEEonmZ1eqmcFGsg053rAx93qj7oOVX3FfMLbsfnZNXFrVodgqRI_SD7oZv5PlDs3XeLSiYapaI9CgIYHP02IyCKe-oSGSzv2qkkB6og2oVdTdx22XQ98T8=','This update announces a second public consultation for Phase 4 of the A629 project, which took place from October 26 to November 23, 2021. It sought feedback on updated proposals for walking, wheeling, cycling, and bus travel improvements between Halifax and Huddersfield. The feedback gathered would be used to refine designs before appointing a contractor, with construction hoped to commence in 2022.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('90b7a6b7-041f-4791-9604-5db2a1e9fbc6','infrastructure-snowhill-retail-park-wakefield-ev-hub',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.322','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'(2025-07-03) This electric car charging point located at Snowhill Retail Park Wakefield Hub, WF1 2DF is part of the Osprey network. There are 8 devices and 8 connectors available at this charging location.','Snowhill Retail Park Wakefield Hub charging point - Zap-Map','Zap-Map','2025-07-03 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG7kTjJY-12LP1T-BJ08hdfCGjd3GqU9Gi7vOCUBzuO-Og9f5qV8A3bP6-B4UM6akXqqFNXNDSYsuqUiq4F2eeaR8dChnvSvrtfhwG2Xwfs4_rhs-r0UFQwWOC92f2lRNcfX5iaxO3nsL_FKjuwoqLynak','Zap-Map provides detailed information on the operational Osprey EV charging hub at Snowhill Retail Park, Wakefield. It confirms the location (WF1 2DF) and states that there are 8 ultra-rapid devices/connectors available, with the information updated on this date.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('90bbac8e-f913-45a4-ad85-1618712fbc5f','infrastructure-home-bargains-garforth-ev-charger',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.429','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'The chargers remained free to use for over two years, until 29th October 2021. [13]','End of Free Charging Period for West Yorkshire\'s EV Network','Carbon Copy / EQUANS','2021-10-29 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH-4f-l8RXP8YU-Zr6bzS-VVDa_gjAk90_Ug66w2flHKMRhOiPnYzk33pRI8WrrhAt1cJ9kHKeMj7MpXZCKiTp7rltckMRCbTNWx64O6fjF27QpCfrQFSeBSD9J_KL_fRk6fIFbprZ_Uox_hHqr4Py6D4wHB8xhXVIljGKqWlc-66kbzlsbceiICAmVNpqH','The initial two-year period of free charging, provided by ENGIE (later EQUANS) across the West Yorkshire Combined Authority\'s EV charging network, concluded on October 29, 2021. After this date, users would likely incur charges for using the public charging points.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('90d95031-467c-4a65-ad63-fe8998df9b53','infrastructure-bp-pulse-stourton-leeds-ev-charger',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.422','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Available facilities listed for BP, Pontefract Road, Leeds, LS10 1SW include: HGV/PSV Fueling, ATM, Air & Water, Convenience Store, 24/7 Opening Hours, Toilet, Electric Car Charging, fuelService. Last updated: 11.09.2025 by PetrolPrices Update Price.','Petrol Prices today at BP, Pontefract Road, Leeds, LS10 1SW','PetrolPrices.com','2025-09-11 00:00:00.000','https://www.petrolprices.com/petrol-stations/bp/pontefract-road-leeds-ls10-1sw','An independent fuel price comparison website, PetrolPrices.com, lists \'Electric Car Charging\' as an available facility at the BP Stourton Service Station, with its information for the station last updated on 2025-09-11.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('90e106ff-df74-42ab-a60f-0c2260e9ebf6','infrastructure-moving-traffic-enforcement-calderdale',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.124','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Almost £125 million investment to improve and maintain West Yorkshire\'s roads over the next two years was agreed this week. ... Meanwhile £8.3m has been earmarked for the Safe Roads programme, which includes new traffic calming measures and improvements to junctions.','Multi-million-pound investment for West Yorkshire roads approved','West Yorkshire Combined Authority','2025-04-04 00:00:00.000','https://www.westyorks-ca.gov.uk/news-and-events/news/multi-million-pound-investment-for-west-yorkshire-roads-approved/','The West Yorkshire Combined Authority approved nearly £125 million for road improvements and maintenance across the region over the next two years. This funding includes £8.3 million specifically allocated to a \'Safe Roads programme\', which aims to introduce new traffic calming measures and improve junctions, complementing wider road safety and traffic flow initiatives.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('90f0b442-03ff-47f0-9f65-1007e3931b64','infrastructure-hebble-brook-halifax-flood-alleviation-scheme',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.231','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Proposed actions to address future flooding were supported by the West Yorkshire Combined Authority at its meeting yesterday. The proposals suggested by the Combined Authority\'s Overview and Scrutiny Committee will inform the wider Flood Review currently being undertaken into the 2015 Boxing Day Floods. They include finding the true total costs of the floods, which affected over 7,000 homes and businesses and put more than 3,600 jobs at risk, and is estimated to cost the Leeds City Region economy up to £365m in 2016. The Plan also emphasises the need to ensuring additional protection for key infrastructure such as electricity substations, which were flooded, leaving thousands of homes, communities and businesses without power for several days. As was the need to build upon positive joint working with Utility Companies such as Yorkshire Water, which rapidly provided additional support to protect key infrastructure and communities.','West Yorkshire Combined Authority supports actions to tackle future floods in Leeds City Region','Calderdale Council – News Centre','2016-09-30 00:00:00.000','https://www.calderdale.gov.uk/news/news-articles/2016/september/west-yorkshire-combined-authority-supports-actions-to-tackle-future-floods.html','The West Yorkshire Combined Authority supported proposed actions to address future flooding, informing a wider Flood Review into the 2015 Boxing Day Floods. The proposals emphasized finding true costs, highlighting community and emergency service responses, and securing additional funding for defences and infrastructure, including working with utility companies like Yorkshire Water.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('90f6d236-41ff-470d-91af-48f6b6812540','infrastructure-copley-village-flood-alleviation-scheme',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.237','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Following completion of the main construction works in Copley village, the BAM team have removed all temporary access routes and wooden fencing from the embankment. The embankment has been built back up and regraded to its original levels, covering the sheet piles that have been installed throughout 2024. ... Although works will be completed in the next few weeks, the embankment will remain closed to the public until at least Summer 2025. This is to allow for grass seeding to be sown and for it to establish. ... Copley FAS – Phase 2. Work to develop a second phase of the scheme is continuing and we hope to submit a planning application for this in the coming months.','Copley Flood Alleviation Scheme (FAS) Information Bulletin No.5 – February 2025','AWS / Environment Agency','2025-02-05 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHyX_cmZMHGnETIUldT6pMNab8rhkxMcsB5cE4wsu2A41ihGHtPi3sxD5ka0v60uJbTAqOu-ZojS5X3NLicrrdshoNlH9kdkq5s5vRnV3m7bNtMrZe2IS8b5Z1M_mlhEsUuQn3T5VoYI5xmw9IaERoef7hZz7f5BL3uMBxZgpdD41F12HiW0l7c22qeEPJElV1tBbgzRWXCeUlnj-UA_GmkCE2vvqwTkzpyAuls8K3Sy9EIjkziNRWxhSdj_KzaWbL95PUciKk=','This bulletin announces the completion of the main construction works in Copley village. The embankment has been rebuilt and regraded but will remain closed to the public until at least Summer 2025 for grass seeding to establish. Development for a second phase of the scheme is continuing.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('914cb3a9-307c-4ed1-afe1-f48d8354d707','infrastructure-halifax-future-high-streets-fund-programme',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.256','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Work is expected to begin in spring 2024 on the £11.7m public realm improvement programme around George Square and George Street, backed by the Future High Streets Fund. ... Calderdale received £18m from the FHSF in December 2020, to support town centre improvements in Halifax (£11.7m) and Elland (£6.3m).','Calderdale gears up for spring start on Halifax public realm improvements','Place Yorkshire','2023-12-19 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGwOI7xAEcTMYUsRX2auMgXgh9f7FfqqQVDqklt6A6DO4DzVOyyuUCIzP1Cg-bmRJPhMOE0stgZvsmOpTvI2lg-xXztm82_HvWkdso_Jy1zM57ZKCiJ0pivNoGG96CSJZ9k9UstHBztFUGD5ahgZBnUs7QcsJsUJJ2xbZJfYnDqfujuTZWViXxp37nd','An announcement that work is expected to begin in spring 2024 on the £11.7m public realm improvement programme around George Square and George Street, funded by the Future High Streets Fund. Plans include creating a new public square, event space, and greener areas.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('9166a592-3d22-4117-b558-9d0db7f6f179','infrastructure-school-streets-initiative-calderdale',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.133','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'After the government announced funding through the Active Travel Fund to introduce School Streets, Kettlethorpe High School was approached to be part of a pilot scheme to introduce School Streets in the Wakefield district. ... Following an initial consultation, a School Street was introduced in September 2021 for a trial period of up to 18 months under an Experimental Traffic Regulation Order (ETRO).','School Street at a Secondary School - Wakefield Council - GOV.UK (Case Study mentioning 2021 launch)','GOV.UK','2021-09-01 00:00:00.000','https://www.gov.uk/government/case-studies/school-street-at-a-secondary-school-wakefield-council','Following successful funding application in November 2020, Wakefield Council launched a School Street trial at Kettlethorpe High School in September 2021 under an Experimental Traffic Regulation Order. The initiative, complementing cycle parking and a Park and Stride location, aimed to improve safety, air quality, and active travel, with positive feedback from students and the community.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('91b88735-0b3b-4fea-b866-febf2c5ef159','infrastructure-darley-street-market',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.082','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'The cost of the three-storey city centre market, handed over by main contractor Kier in June, has gone up by a further £2.42m as the city battles to bring flagship projects to fruition. ... The overall cost of the three-storey market had already climbed from around £23m to £27m, with a further £1.4m already signed off. ... The project was started in April 2021, and the main construction phase has been completed. However, several factors, as outlined in the report to the executive, have impacted the project. These included design changes and additional work during the demolition phase, when foundations of surrounding buildings were exposed following the demolition of the M&S building, meaning temporary and permanent propping-up was required.','Cash-strapped Bradford to top up Darley Street funding','Place Yorkshire','2024-08-29 00:00:00.000','https://placeyorkshire.uk/','Bradford Council approved an additional £2.42 million in funding for the Darley Street Market project due to increased costs and complexities during construction. This added to previous budget increases, with the total cost having already risen from approximately £23 million to £27 million, plus an earlier £1.4 million approval. Despite the financial challenges, the market was anticipated to open in early 2025, with strong interest from traders.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('91c73b71-7ad4-4da1-8f4a-88ec3a67b8a4','infrastructure-a660-holt-lane--otley-road-junction-improvements-adel-leeds',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:19.964','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'A consultation on plans to introduce traffic signals to the Holt Lane and Otley Road junction was undertaken, with feedback closing on 3rd August 2018. [7, 8]','Proposals for the Holt Lane and Otley Road junction - Public Consultation','Commonplace (Adel To Leeds Route)','2018-07-10 00:00:00.000','https://a660qtc.commonplace.is/schemes/proposals/proposals-for-the-holt-lane-and-otley-road-junction/details','This Commonplace platform hosts details about a public consultation on plans to introduce traffic signals and other changes to the Holt Lane and Otley Road junction as part of the wider Adel to Leeds Route improvements. The consultation closed on 3rd August 2018.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('91e1ec1d-46c0-4fdd-9bfc-23aa7d9e2309','infrastructure-a629-halifax-town-centre-corridor-improvement-phase-2-calderdale',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:19.902','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'The Full Business Case for the A629 Halifax Town Centre Corridor Improvement (Phase 2) project was submitted in July 2020, and a final funding decision was approved by the West Yorkshire Combined Authority\'s Investment Committee in early November 2020. This approval paved the way for the release of a construction tender.','A629 Phase 2 Halifax Town Centre project funding approved by West Yorkshire Combined Authority','Calderdale Next Chapter','2020-11-01 00:00:00.000','https://calderdalenextchapter.co.uk/projects/a629-halifax-town-centre/','The Full Business Case for the A629 Halifax Town Centre Corridor Improvement (Phase 2) project was submitted in July 2020, and a final funding decision was approved by the West Yorkshire Combined Authority\'s Investment Committee in early November 2020. This approval paved the way for the release of a construction tender.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('9243e01c-64c9-4c7e-84f5-a27244fcbb21','infrastructure-west-yorkshire-plus-transport-fund-programme',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:19.788','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'West Yorkshire Combined Authority\'s Transport Fund has been partly funded through the Leeds City Region Enterprise Partnership (LEP) Growth Deal. A £1 billion package of Government funding to drive growth and job creation across the Leeds City Region. The aim is to create around 20,000 new jobs and add £2.4 billion a year to the economy by the mid-2030s. Major transport improvements in Calderdale include: A629 Salterhebble to Shaw Hill (Phase 1a). A629 Calder and Hebble Junction (Phase 1b). A629 Halifax Town Centre (Phase 2). A629 Halifax to Huddersfield (Phase 4). A629 Ainley Top to Huddersfield (Phase 5 - Kirklees led). Halifax rail station. Elland rail station. A641 Bradford - Brighouse - Huddersfield. [14]','West Yorkshire Plus Transport Fund (Calderdale Council Update)','Calderdale Council','2025-02-11 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHbVypHtS6pAX6jh7b6WES0xlvpFSSkvpkIMzVLHIPqRrVH_hriVdsFHTasp-c5MxhYRyWR5mW_b8UKJllu2hNZGjOIMHy2RQsrvvmcb9366GwI5m2enVOf-4KtXYHg5r5J214ZPO08mZNFkSVlx3gVE7mwvTdC7eapMygpPg5exObjSAFR0XmMg-t85mjsYIq1n_phX8Xf4fXyCDG2VjmbLPLn_PJo0w==','Calderdale Council provides an update on its transformation efforts, highlighting major transport improvements funded by the West Yorkshire Combined Authority\'s Transport Fund. These include various phases of the A629 scheme (Salterhebble to Shaw Hill, Calder and Hebble Junction, Halifax Town Centre, Halifax to Huddersfield, Ainley Top to Huddersfield), as well as projects for Halifax rail station, Elland rail station, and the A641 Bradford - Brighouse - Huddersfield corridor. The fund aims to create around 20,000 new jobs and add £2.4 billion a year to the economy by the mid-2030s. [14]','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('9265d650-c1b9-4ac5-acf1-79d29bf1aa0e','infrastructure-five-towns-leisure-hub-wakefield',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.669','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'The new Five Towns Leisure and Wellbeing Hub, which is going to be called Aspire@ThePark, was originally expected to be ready for business by the autumn of this year. But a major flood hit the site before last Christmas, when Yorkshire Water were working on pipes underneath the centre\'s 3G pitch. As a result, progress on the building stalled. Despite this, Wakefield Council says the development is now continuing at pace and will open early next year. The new £21m leisure centre at Pontefract Park will now not be open until 2021, it has emerged. [6]','Opening of new £21m Five Towns Leisure Centre in Pontefract delayed until 2021','Wakefield Express','2020-03-18 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAHvRP5U52lJPz7SXYhg8dsxG-A9TfE0Af6BduVWwcB6JPgnHSW82B2bQxA28E1FGZNlU4pWHea7DSJcdGs8A5jF30m2W_59s98jKHjfoLcZ9TzaQWUQa85RgRHV3Rc3jX6Bj7Q35pTCbsTHQwfAFsOT8PMdcn3ehx5ddrifEo3n5dzkQ_2_68vpuAx9iy4FK-ezVJnPZBsWHMC1isBZehrjiHtdeULYub_v0ks-iEsxGovpu9RYKpcgd4nuZg5ozWh2boNg74DY2RhQ=','The opening of the new Five Towns Leisure and Wellbeing Hub, to be named Aspire@ThePark, was delayed from autumn 2020 until early 2021. The setback was attributed to a major flood that hit the site before Christmas 2019. Despite this, Wakefield Council stated that construction was continuing at pace for the £21 million project.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('92a903e9-d602-469e-9155-9ac5bdc9cbef','infrastructure-todmorden-area-a646-corridor-improvements-calderdale',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:19.925','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'Calderdale Council and the West Yorkshire Combined Authority are developing a series of improvements to the road network along the A58 / A672 from Junction 22 of the M62 to King Cross in Halifax and the A646 / A6033 from Todmorden to Skircoat Moor. ... Here we take a closer at what is being planned on the A646 corridor which will cost £5.09m. ... The consultation on the plans will run until February 14. Construction is proposed to take place from autumn 2020.','A Closer Look at £5m A646 Corridor Improvements in Calderdale','Halifax Courier','2020-01-22 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFEc8qcfnJe0rwl3jRTprLwS7xL7bpnHXT_iYBQDf-Gj_01xytxCqolqbobuxSGROf8MQMjqqeXw4gWaAwaZiMqnFhBQTXwoo0B0EdIz5QVG5LFuolcGLimdiAhTMEHtFNHclr0q2y5qrhMWPt7tAIjfyDD2ofKZruU0QHBqyc8YhLZVPDbGj69lnsU1drifhnuWarGDqKjk7O7a6frm8uMsqcwS8k4avJAEvwXqBT9ISI5Gpy9T-XookWL42jhAH7ElnG8GVHoTIZml_FmCA==','The Halifax Courier reported on the £5.09 million A646 Corridor Improvement scheme, detailing its aims to improve journey time reliability, air quality, accident reduction, and enable housing growth. Specific proposals for Todmorden included a pedestrianised area, changes to crossings, and bus stop relocation. Public consultation was set to run until February 14, 2020, with construction anticipated from autumn 2020.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901'),
	('93ba90ce-e29d-4ce3-860d-2a288f141175','infrastructure-residents-parking-zones-calderdale',1,'TEXT','2025-09-18 12:50:20.129','APPROVED',NULL,NULL,'A petition calling on Calderdale Council to create more parking in the town has received support from shop owners, who say there simply aren\'t enough spaces and that the future of their businesses will be put at risk unless action is taken. ... In a statement, the Hebden Bridge Business Forum said: \'We definitely back improvement to the parking provision in Hebden Royd, and indeed other solutions such as provision of e-bikes and exploring park and ride options. \'Calderdale Council asked for the input of local businesses at the parking strategy meeting we held on February 7, so we do know that there is commitment to find solutions to the parking issue, which is encouraging.\'','Hebden Bridge business owners warn the town could suffer unless action is taken on lack of parking spaces - Halifax Courier','Halifax Courier','2024-03-21 00:00:00.000','https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEmNKOLRBrxiqx_KdH-V21NrmVeK90Qx7x8CxB3asYCwQMNIxcsarYCwpwFaPiAe1bu8erv_XDHBZ7NOid5SeAD1dfK9gXJkGdp1DAszoqb2uype5POz6Jy4P9E2wWjhzw4bvbjDy0ImFSp6XJyvZRFrRL5pk_te_LiMtkkdjCTnUifP0zdrPgJ1D5Hfquow2RWlxCOn21T2Nzf5SPMMCS6sluK2eoyPwZ2bUjFAKWa4Bz8JYhuN__FQ58Mps3XzJPNqllk6cgwha3kdfH2Y0EsOKPP0pLcCg==','This news report highlights concerns from Hebden Bridge business owners and residents regarding a lack of parking spaces and the impact of increasing parking charges. It references a parking strategy meeting held on February 7, 2024, where Calderdale Council sought input from local businesses, confirming ongoing community engagement about parking issues, which would encompass residential parking.','2025-09-18 20:51:57.901');
