	('infrastructure-west-yorkshire-places-scheme-cornholme-a646-active-travel','West Yorkshire Places Scheme (Cornholme A646 Active Travel)','Active travel improvements in Cornholme, including new footway links along the A646, pedestrian crossings, and a one-way system on Greenfield Terrace.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 11:01:54.560',NULL,'GREEN','2025-09-19 07:23:59.051','The project has completed its public consultation (March-April 2025) and is on schedule for outcome reports in October 2025, with physical delivery projected to start in March 2026, aligning with the published timeline.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-19 07:23:59.052','The project focuses on active travel improvements in Cornholme, a village in Calderdale, West Yorkshire. Key areas include new footway links along the A646 and a one-way system on Greenfield Terrace, near Cornholme Junior, Infant and Nursery School (OL14 8PL). Specific latitude and longitude coordinates could not be programmatically extracted.','West Yorkshire Combined Authority (e.g., Your Voice platform)','LOW'),
	('infrastructure-west-yorkshire-plus-transport-fund-programme','West Yorkshire-plus Transport Fund Programme','A £1 billion 20-year commitment for strategic transport projects across Leeds City Region to enable development and create jobs.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 10:23:04.442',NULL,'GREEN','2025-09-19 07:24:18.934','The project secured a significant £2.1 billion funding boost in June 2025, enabling work to begin on the region\'s tram project by 2028 and supporting other critical transport infrastructure. Strong public support for the tram system has also been confirmed.',53.8012770,-1.5485670,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-19 07:24:18.936','Leeds City Centre, West Yorkshire, United Kingdom','Latitude and longitude coordinates for Leeds, UK','MEDIUM'),
	('infrastructure-west-yorkshire-transforming-cities-fund-programme','West Yorkshire Transforming Cities Fund Programme','A £317 million fund plus local match funding for transport infrastructure, prioritising accessible, attractive, and cleaner alternatives to car journeys.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 10:23:07.604',NULL,'GREEN','2025-09-16 10:23:07.604',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-18 20:45:36.462',NULL,NULL,NULL),
	('infrastructure-westgate-phase-2-and-palatine-chambers-halifax','Westgate Phase 2 and Palatine Chambers (Halifax)','Regeneration project in Halifax bringing derelict land and buildings back into use for high-quality business spaces and public realm improvements.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 11:14:19.766',NULL,'GREEN','2025-09-19 07:29:28.922','The \'Westgate Phase II\' project, part of the larger regeneration, is anticipated to reach a \'shell and core finish\' in November 2025, with tenants already applying for licenses and advertising for staff. This indicates significant progress towards completion and imminent operational readiness.',53.7259000,-1.8601000,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-19 07:29:28.946','Halifax town centre, specifically the area formerly housing Horton House on Horton Street.','Halifax Courier','HIGH'),
	('infrastructure-white-rose-rail-station-leeds','White Rose Rail Station (Leeds)','New railway station between Morley and Cottingley, providing access near the White Rose Shopping Centre. Includes a park-and-ride facility.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 11:59:10.904',NULL,'AMBER','2025-09-19 07:29:33.033','No evidence timeline was provided to assess the project\'s current progress.',53.7610000,-1.5790000,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-19 07:29:33.035','The planned White Rose railway station is located in south Leeds, England, near the White Rose Shopping Centre and White Rose Office Park, between Cottingley and Morley railway stations on the Huddersfield Line.','Wikipedia','HIGH'),
	('infrastructure-woolpack-inn-leeds-ev-charger','Woolpack Inn Leeds EV Charger','Electric vehicle charging point at Woolpack Inn, Leeds.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 11:31:22.283',NULL,'GREEN','2025-09-19 07:29:44.784','The project is active and operational, as confirmed by the Zapmap listing update on 2025-08-27, which indicates the electric vehicle charging point is current and part of the Osprey network.',53.8687000,-1.6917000,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-19 07:29:44.785','Woolpack Inn, 18 New Road, Yeadon, Leeds, LS19 7SE.','Zapmap, The Woolpack Website, ChargeFinder, Electromaps, Google Search (for coordinates)','HIGH'),
	('infrastructure-wyke-beck-flood-alleviation-scheme','Wyke Beck Flood Alleviation Scheme','£2.6 million investment in East Leeds to implement flood protection measures, safeguarding local properties and businesses from flood risk.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 11:47:29.144',NULL,'GREEN','2025-09-16 11:47:29.144',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-18 20:45:36.462',NULL,NULL,NULL),
	('infrastructure-yorkshire-water-amp8-infrastructure-programme','Yorkshire Water AMP8 Infrastructure Programme','£2.8 billion investment from April 2025-March 2030 for water distribution networks, sewer pipes, and a significant reduction in stormwater overflows into natural watercourses.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 11:48:27.429',NULL,'GREEN','2025-09-19 08:48:01.998','Ofwat has approved £8.3 billion for Yorkshire Water\'s 2025-2030 plan, surpassing the initial £2.8 billion. Contractors are appointed, and significant investments in storm overflow reduction are underway across the region, indicating strong progress.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-19 08:48:02.010','The project encompasses Yorkshire Water\'s entire service region, which includes West Yorkshire, South Yorkshire, the East Riding of Yorkshire, most of North Yorkshire, and parts of North Lincolnshire and Derbyshire. Specific ongoing projects are mentioned in locations such as Sheffield, Northallerton, and Marton, all within Yorkshire, UK.','Water & Wastewater Treatment (WWT); Wikipedia - Yorkshire Water','LOW'),
	('infrastructure-zapmap-ring-road-middleton-leeds-ev-charger','Zapmap Ring Road Middleton Leeds EV Charger','Electric vehicle charging point at Ring Road, Middleton, Leeds.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 11:33:42.328',NULL,'GREEN','2025-09-19 08:48:09.561','Two operational EV charging points matching the project description (Ring Road, Middleton, Leeds) are listed on Zapmap, with recent updates (September 13, 2025 for Asda, August 1, 2025 for Aldi).',53.7489550,-1.5286950,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-19 08:48:09.563','Asda Middleton Superstore, Holme Well Road, Middleton, Leeds, LS10 4TQ. This postcode also covers Aldi St George\'s Retail Park, Middleton.','Open Postcode Geo via GetTheData.com','HIGH'),
	('infrastructure-zapmap-spinning-acres-lane-headingley-ev-charger','Zapmap Spinning Acres Lane Headingley EV Charger','Electric vehicle charging point at Spinning Acres Lane, Headingley, Leeds.','LOCAL_GOV',NULL,NULL,1,'2025-09-16 11:34:45.602',NULL,'AMBER','2025-09-19 08:48:21.713','No evidence was provided regarding the project\'s real-world status. Precise coordinates for the EV charger location at The Spool House, LS6 4FN, could not be directly extracted from web search results.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'PENDING','2025-09-19 08:48:21.714','The Spool House, Spinning Acres Lane, Headingley, Leeds, LS6 4FN.','Pickard Properties (via Google Search)','LOW'),
